00:08:34.064 --> 00:08:37.554
And it recognizes a peptide in a groove of a major

156
00:08:37.554 --> 00:08:38.784
histocompatibility complex. And that's what happens.

157
00:08:39.024 --> 00:08:41.404
Now, something that I've been inspired about since I was a graduate student is that

158
00:08:41.444 --> 00:08:45.213
despite the fact that we go through all of this work to make an exquisitely

159
00:08:45.324 --> 00:08:48.284
specific T cell receptor or T cells, the really interesting thing is that if a T

160
00:08:48.344 --> 00:08:52.294
cell sees its antigen by itself, it actually turns the T cell off, not

161
00:08:52.294 --> 00:08:52.444
