00:09:21.974 --> 00:09:23.574
after the cell gets triggered through its T cell receptor.

172
00:09:24.604 --> 00:09:26.244
But it's not just co-stimulation.

173
00:09:26.264 --> 00:09:29.304
There's also the other side of the axis in the sense of

174
00:09:29.364 --> 00:09:31.604
co-inhibition or checkpoint molecules.

175
00:09:31.844 --> 00:09:34.164
These are the ones that you probably read about in The New York Times and have seen

176
00:09:34.204 --> 00:09:38.164
while you're here at AACR. CTLA-4, PD-1, or suppressor

