00:09:42.984 --> 00:09:45.804
So these are traditionally called co-stimulation and co-inhibition.

179
00:09:45.844 --> 00:09:48.084
T cells get context from the target.

180
00:09:48.324 --> 00:09:51.644
The antigen is being expressed by a target cell, but the target cell is actually

181
00:09:51.724 --> 00:09:55.564
telling the cell whether or not to stand down or to activate.

182
00:09:57.224 --> 00:10:01.164
The '90s and the 2000s saw an entirely new wave of immunoregulation

183
00:10:01.444 --> 00:10:05.104
of cloning these co-stimulatory and co-inhibitory molecules,

184
00:10:05.624 --> 00:10:09.424
figuring out their signaling, their downstream transcriptional activity, and how

185
00:10:09.504 --> 00:10:12.224
it modified the activity of the T cell.

186
00:10:13.444 --> 00:10:16.424
Now, this is a massive oversimplification, but the term

187
00:10:16.524 --> 00:10:20.404
co-stimulation is essentially the cell adding up

