00:39:06.644 --> 00:39:10.584
antibody that's been shown to be very powerful and potent in cancer patients,

672
00:39:11.244 --> 00:39:13.704
to this TIL therapy that I just told you about.

673
00:39:13.724 --> 00:39:17.384
And you can appreciate, very visually obvious here, that

674
00:39:17.424 --> 00:39:21.164
progression-free survival at six months was drastically

675
00:39:21.204 --> 00:39:23.804
different between patients that got the TIL therapy at

676
00:39:24.024 --> 00:39:27.484
52.7% versus that of patients that got ipilimumab.

677
00:39:28.544 --> 00:39:30.264
As a consequence of this finding,

678
00:39:31.164 --> 00:39:34.964
it motivated a lot of investigators to really understand that

679
00:39:35.004 --> 00:39:38.504
this is a clinically meaningful result and is now FDA approved.

680
00:39:38.864 --> 00:39:42.624
Patients at the Winship Cancer Institute, for example, at Emory, get

681
00:39:42.684 --> 00:39:46.664
this therapy. And this is restricted at the moment to patients

682
00:39:46.704 --> 00:39:50.654
with metastatic melanoma, but coming down the pipeline will be patients treated

683
00:39:50.684 --> 00:39:54.364
with head and neck cancer. And, I think, quite

684
00:39:54.404 --> 00:39:55.924
honestly, the world is our oyster.

685
00:39:55.964 --> 00:39:59.904
We can really start understanding how can we manipulate these TIL

686
00:40:00.024 --> 00:40:02.704
therapeutic products in a way to make therapies

687
00:40:02.724 --> 00:40:06.584
better. So now I'm going to walk you through

688
00:40:07.344 --> 00:40:10.004
four different types of adoptive immunotherapy.

689
00:40:11.024 --> 00:40:14.544
And this slide was made by my former graduate student, Aubrey Smith.

