00:41:27.074 --> 00:41:31.004
antigen against NY-ESO, and expanded them to very

710
00:41:31.044 --> 00:41:34.584
large numbers and put them into patients, and saw really potent anti-tumor

711
00:41:34.604 --> 00:41:37.884
responses in some of these individuals.

712
00:41:38.804 --> 00:41:42.184
But there's a trick here, and one thing that the tumor

713
00:41:42.244 --> 00:41:46.224
microenvironment does and what a cancer likes to do is hide

714
00:41:46.264 --> 00:41:50.104
itself. And one way in which it does that, it will down-regulate

715
00:41:50.184 --> 00:41:53.874
MHC. So what do you do? How do you use TIL therapy

716
00:41:53.904 --> 00:41:57.824
or what we've learned about TIL therapy to make a difference in

717
00:41:57.884 --> 00:41:59.004
these types of patients?

718
00:42:00.104 --> 00:42:04.084
Tumors also express this protein on their cell surface.

719
00:42:04.684 --> 00:42:07.384
We can detect tumor antigen in this way, too.

720
00:42:07.484 --> 00:42:10.674
